---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Thunder Bay AI automation | ThunderBayAI" description="AI automation strategy for Thunder Bay businesses looking to reduce manual work, improve lead response, and build cleaner systems.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container split-panel">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Primary keyword: Thunder Bay AI automation</p>
        <h1>Thunder Bay AI automation for businesses losing time to manual work and slow follow-up.</h1>
        <p class="lead">AI automation is only valuable when it improves a real workflow: missed-call follow-up, quote requests, appointment booking, customer updates, lead qualification, CRM handoff, or repetitive admin.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button" href="/ai-opportunity-audit">Get a Free AI Opportunity Audit</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="https://frayze.ca/contact/">See What You Can Automate</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Where businesses start</p>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>Missed calls are not being recovered quickly enough.</li>
          <li>Leads sit in inboxes or text threads with no process.</li>
          <li>Staff waste hours on repetitive updates and handoffs.</li>
          <li>There is no reliable system connecting forms, calls, and follow-up.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container grid grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>What Thunder Bay businesses can automate first</h2>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>missed-call text back and routing</li>
          <li>lead capture from forms and chat</li>
          <li>estimate request follow-up</li>
          <li>appointment reminders and no-show reduction</li>
          <li>review request workflows</li>
          <li>internal admin and status updates</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Best fit</h2>
        <p class="muted">Contractors, home services, automotive, restaurants, and local service businesses with real lead flow and visible operational drag.</p>
        <p class="inline-note">If the business already has demand but weak response systems, automation usually creates faster ROI than chasing more traffic first.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Related pathways</h2>
        <p class="muted">AI automation works best when tied to a stronger CRM, cleaner website conversion flow, and local lead generation system.</p>
        <div class="kicker-bar">
          <a class="kicker-chip" href="/thunder-bay-crm-systems">Thunder Bay CRM systems</a>
          <a class="kicker-chip" href="/thunder-bay-website-systems">Thunder Bay website systems</a>
          <a class="kicker-chip" href="/thunder-bay-lead-generation-systems">Thunder Bay lead generation systems</a>
          <a class="kicker-chip" href="/contractor-crm-automation-thunder-bay">Contractor CRM automation</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
